{{Infobox organization | name = Comitato Giovani Sordi Italiani | image = | image_border = | size = <!-- default 200px --> | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = | map2 = | abbreviation = | formation = {{Start date and age|1994}}<ref>[http://www.cgsi-italia.it/chi-siamo/membri-passati LA STORIA DEL COMITATO GIOVANI SORDI ITALIANI]</ref> | extinction = <!-- {{End date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | type = [[National nongovernmental organization]] | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = Human, Civil, and Linguistic rights of Deaf people. | headquarters = [[Rome]], Italy | location = Rome, Via Gregorio VII, 120 | coords = | region_served = National | membership = 400 | leader_title = President | leader_name = [[Gianteodoro Pisciottani]] | leader_title2 = Vice President | leader_name2 = [[Katia Bugé]] | main_organ = Board | affiliations = | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = {{url|http://www.cgsi-italia.it/}} }}
The '''Comitato Giovani Sordi Italiani''' ('''CGSI''') is an Italian [[non-governmental organization]] that acts as a [[peak body]] for [[National Association of the Deaf (Italy)|national associations of Deaf people]], with a focus on Deaf young people who use sign language<ref>[http://www.ilmamilio.it/m/it/comuni/altri-comuni/fuori-zona/22441-il-comitato-giovani-sordi-italiani-festeggia-il-20%C2%B0-anniversario.html IL MAMILIO: il CGSI festeggia 20° anniversario]</ref> and their family and friends.<ref>[http://www.iltempo.it/rubriche/salute/2014/09/19/il-comitato-giovani-sordi-italiani-festeggia-20-anni-1.1312544 IL TEMPO.IT: Festeggia il CGSI 20 anni]</ref> CGSI aims to promote the Human Rights of Deaf Youngs Italians,<ref>[http://www.cgsi-italia.it/images/aggiornamento_20_anniversario/Eventuali_giornali/Tivoli_CGSI.pdf TIVOLI CGSI]</ref> by working closely with the [[Italy]]. CGSI is also a member of the [[World Federation of the Deaf - Youth Section]] (WFDYS) and [[European Union of the Deaf Youth]] (EUDY).
==History== The CGSI was established on 14 May 1994 in [[Aosta]],<ref>{{it}} [http://www.storiadeisordi.it/acrobat/storiaCGSI.pdf La storia del CGSI]</ref> [[Italy]], at the first meeting of the Deaf young Italians, under the auspices of ''Gruppi Giovanili Sordomuti'' of the [[Ente Nazionale Sordi]], the Italian Deaf Association. The first president of CGSI was [[Francesco Piccigallo]], who was also, at that time.
