{{Multiple issues|{{BLP sources|date=April 2016}}{{citation style|date=April 2016}}}}

'''Howard Teicher''' served as Director for the Near East and South Asia and Senior Director for Political-Military Affairs on the staff of the [[United States National Security Council|National Security Council]] from 1982 to 1987, after working under Presidents [[Jimmy Carter]] and [[Ronald Reagan]] at the Departments of State and Defense.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20141010103823/http://www.historycommons.org/entity.jsp?entity=howard_teicher A profile of Teicher.]</ref>

Teicher received his BA in Political Science, summa cum laude and [[Phi Beta Kappa]], from Boston University in 1976. He received a Masters in International Affairs from Johns Hopkins University School of Advanced International Studies in 1978. Teicher is currently Vice President with [[Radware]].<ref>[http://www.afcea.org/sourcebook/details.jsp?dir=L&cid=55179456&keywords= AFCEA]</ref>

He is the co-author of ''Twin Pillars To Desert Storm: America's Flawed Vision in the Middle East from Nixon to Bush''.<ref>[http://www.foreignaffairs.com/author/howard-teicher ''Twin Pillars'' on Foreign Affairs.]</ref>

