{{Infobox political party | name = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | lang1 = Finnish | name_lang1 = {{Lang|fi|Seitsemän tähden liike}} | lang2 = Swedish | name_lang2 = {{Lang|sv|Sju stjärnors rörelsen}} | lang3 = | name_lang3 = | lang4 = | name_lang4 = | logo = Seven Star Movement.png | logo_size = | caption = | colorcode = {{Seven Star Movement/meta/color}}<!-- HTML color code (e.g. "red", "#FF0000" or Party metadata color template) otherwise "transparent" --> | abbreviation = <!-- official abbreviation --> | leader = | president = [[Paavo Väyrynen]] | chairperson = <!-- or: | chairman = --> | general_secretary = | first_secretary = | secretary_general = | presidium = | secretary = [[Seppo Hauta-aho]] | spokesperson = | founder = | leader1_title = | leader1_name = | leader2_title = | leader2_name = | leader3_title = | leader3_name = | leader4_title = | leader4_name = | leader5_title = | leader5_name = | founded = {{start date|2018||}} | legalised = <!-- or |legalized= --> | dissolved = <!-- {{end date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merger = | split = [[Citizens' Party (Finland)|Citizens' Party]] | predecessor = | merged = | successor = | headquarters = [[Helsinki]] | newspaper = | think_tank = | student_wing = | youth_wing = | womens_wing = | wing1_title = | wing1 = | wing2_title = | wing2 = | wing3_title = | wing3 = | wing4_title = | wing4 = | membership_year = | membership = | ideology = [[Political independence]], [[Neutral country|non-alignment]], [[anti-immigration]] | position = | religion = | national = | regional = | european = | continental = | international = | europarl = | affiliation1_title = | affiliation1 = | colors = <!-- or: | colours = --> | slogan = | anthem = | blank1_title = | blank1 = | blank2_title = | blank2 = | blank3_title = | blank3 = | blank4_title = | blank4 = | seats1_title = [[Parliament of Finland]] | seats1 = {{Infobox political party/seats|1|200|hex={{Seven Star Movement/meta/color}}}} | seats2_title = | seats2 = | seats3_title = | seats3 = | seats4_title = | seats4 = <!-- up to |seats15= --> | symbol = | flag = | website = {{Official URL}} | state = <!-- or country --> | country = Finland | country_dab1 = | parties_dab1 = | elections_dab1 = | country2 = | country_dab2 = | parties_dab2 = | elections_dab2 = | footnotes = }} '''Seven Star Movement''' ({{lang-fi|Seitsemän tähden liike}},<ref name=EU/> {{lang-sv|Sju stjärnors rörelsen}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=HS: Paavo Väyrynen misstänkts använda e-postlista från sitt förra parti - 'Uppgifterna är stulna' säger Medborgarpartiet |last=Pettersson |first=Dann |work=Yle News |date=1 August 2018 |access-date=19 November 2018 |url= https://svenska.yle.fi/artikel/2018/08/01/hs-paavo-vayrynen-misstankts-anvanda-e-postlista-fran-sitt-forra-parti |language=sv}}</ref>) is an unregistered political party in Finland founded in 2018. The party was founded by [[Paavo Väyrynen]], its president and only MP, after he was ousted from his previous party, [[Citizens' Party (Finland)|Citizens' Party]].
==History== [[Paavo Väyrynen]] had successfully run for the [[Finnish Parliament]] in the [[Finnish parliamentary election, 2015]], representing the [[Centre Party (Finland)|Centre Party]]. Väyrynen, however, chose to forfeit his seat in order to serve in the [[European Parliament]] that he had entered earlier.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Paavo Väyrynen palasi eduskuntaan |last=Lehto |first=Mika |work=Ilta-Sanomat |date=12 June 2018 |access-date=19 November 2018 |url= https://www.is.fi/politiikka/art-2000005716018.html |language=fi }}</ref> Väyrynen returned to the Finnish Parliament in June 2018, but defected from the Centre Party to [[Citizens' Party (Finland)|Citizens' Party]] which he had founded. The party was, however, already at that time engulfed in a power struggle that resulted in Väyrynen's ouster. In late June, Väyrynen announced that he had founded the Seven Star Movement as a substitute for Citizens' Party, with which he remained in the parliament for a time. The name is inspired by the populist Italian [[Five Star Movement]]. The Seven Star Movement's goals are [[political independence]], [[Neutral country|non-alignment]], and greater [[immigration control]].<ref name=Centre>{{Cite web |title=Ex-Centre elder Paavo Väyrynen sets up yet another party |work=Yle News |date=27 July 2018 |access-date=19 November 2018 |url= https://yle.fi/uutiset/osasto/news/ex-centre_elder_paavo_vayrynen_sets_up_yet_another_party/10326386 }}</ref>
A trial court ruled in November 2018 that Väyrynen's ouster had been illegal.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kansalaispuolue aikoo valittaa hoviin ratkaisusta, jonka mukaan Väyrysen erottaminen oli laiton – 'Mahdoton hyväksyä' |last=de Fresnes |first=Tulikukka |work=Yle News |date=6 November 2018 |access-date=19 November 2018 |url= https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-10494408 |language=fi }}</ref> Despite the ruling, the legal woes promoted Väyrynen to go forward with his Seven Star Movement rather than Citizens' Party. Later that month, Väyrynen announced that he had officially aligned himself with the {{ill|Seven Star Movement's parliamentary group|fi|Tähtiliikkeen eduskuntaryhmä}}, whose only MP he became.<ref name=EU/> Väyrynen is the president of the party. The secretary is [[Seppo Hauta-aho]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Yhteystiedot |publisher=Seven Star Movement |work=Seitsemän tähden liike |date=2018 |access-date=19 November 2018 |url= http://xn--seitsemnthdenliike-rtbc.fi/yhteystiedot/ |language=fi }}</ref> Väyrynen's former campaign aide.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Paavo Väyrysen kampanjapäällikkö Seppo Hauta-aho: Erottamisjupakassa on kyse 38 000 eurosta - 'vähän sekava tilanne' |last=Waris |first=Olli |work=Iltalehti |date=3 March 2018 |access-date=19 November 2018 |url= https://www.iltalehti.fi/politiikka/a/201803032200786096 |language=fi }}</ref> The party is based in [[Helsinki]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Seitsemän tähden liike ry/rp:n säännöt|publisher=Seven Star Movement |work=Seitsemän tähden liike |date=2018 |access-date=19 November 2018 |url= http://seitsemäntähdenliike.fi/upload/File/Seitsem%C3%A4n_t%C3%A4hden_liike_ry_s%C3%A4%C3%A4nn%C3%B6t.pdf?580264 |language=fi }}</ref>
The movement is gathering supporter cards in order to be admitted to the {{Ill|party register|fi|Puoluerekisteri}}. {{As of|2018|11}}, it has 3,500 out of the required 5,000 cards. The party plans to take part in the [[Finnish parliamentary election, 2019]] and the [[European Parliament election, 2019|European Parliamentary election the same year]]. Väyrynen himself has stated that he is "possibly" running for parliament but not for the European Parliament because his wife,<ref name=EU>{{Cite web |title=Väyrynen ei ehdolle EU-vaaleihin, eduskuntavaaliehdokkuus 'mahdollista' |last=Ruokangas |first=Perttu |work=Yle News |date=16 November 2018 |access-date=19 November 2018 |url= https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-10511944 |language=fi}}</ref> [[Vuokko Väyrynen]], has been diagnosed with [[plasma cell myeloma]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tällainen sairaus on Paavo Väyrysen Vuokko-vaimon verisyöpä – 'Ei nykytiedon valossa voi täysin parantaa' |last=Kujala |first=Piia |work=Ilta-Sanomat |date=5 November 2018 |access-date=19 November 2018 |url= https://www.is.fi/kotimaa/art-2000005889228.html |language=fi }}</ref>
